page.title: 03Types of Housing in March.
page.content: By the{River}Nene,in{West End,}there} is a{modern detached house}built in the{Dutch style,}and also a Dutch style cottage called{Vandermoyden {Cottage}which has the{date MDCXCV} (1695) on it. This is probably the oldest house in our 'block'.We feel this is a clear reminder of the draining of the Fens by the{Dutch {engineers. There is a{hostel for mentally {handicapped people in Elm Road, which is a modern building. There are some{bungalows}called Swan Court,which are for{elderly people. There was once a maternity home in March,but it is now a home for elderly people.Also for old people were some {flats}which we discovered in{St.John's {Chase. We even have well-established{caravan {homes}in{Robingoodfellows Lane.
